Claims Claims The claims defining the invention are as follows: 1 . A display device for vehicles, comprising: a. a display sheet comprising a plurality of display regions, a first end region, and a second end region; b. a housing having an interior space, the display sheet being located within the interior space, one face of the housing being comprised of a transparent material which allows viewing of a display region of the plurality of display regions; c. a first shaft comprising a first and a second end region rotatably mounted to the housing, and a first rotator, the first rotator being configured to rotate the first end region of the first shaft, and the first end region of the display sheet being detachably attached to the first shaft in such a way that when the first shaft rotates, the display sheet either rolls onto the first shaft or unrolls outward the first shaft; d. a second shaft comprising a first and a second end region rotatably mounted to the housing, e. a motor fixed inside the housing and directly or indirectly mechanically connected to the first rotator; f. one or more power sources for powering the motor; g. a controller powered by one of the one or more power sources, the controller comprising a memory and a processor, the memory being operatively connected to the processor and storing computer-executable instructions, wherein the controller is operably coupled to the motor, such that the processor may execute the computer-executable instructions to activate the motor to: i. rotate the first rotator in a clockwise direction; or ii. rotate the first rotator in a counterclockwise direction. 2. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , further comprising a second rotator, the second rotator being configured to rotate the first end region of the second shaft; the second rotator being connected to the first rotator in such a way that when the first rotator is rotated, the second rotator also rotates in the same direction, and the 

 second end region of the display sheet being detachably attached to the second shaft in such a way that when the second shaft rotates, the display sheet either rolls onto the second shaft or unrolls outward the second shaft. 3. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , further comprising a signal receiving device and a remote device, wherein the remote device can be operated by a user to send a signal to the signal receiving device and wherein the computer executable instructions are configured, on receipt of the signal at the signal receiving device, to activate the motor to: i. rotate the first rotator in a clockwise direction; or ii. rotate the first rotator in a counterclockwise direction. 4. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the memory of the controller comprises a user profile module. 5. The display device for vehicles of claim 3, wherein the remote device operated by the user comprises a user profile module. 6. The display device for vehicles of claim 5, wherein the user profile module is configured to track a data related to date, time, and distance travelled by a user when each of the plurality of display regions is in use and record the data in a logbook. 7. The display device for vehicles of claim 6, wherein the user profile module is configured to transmit the data from the logbook to one or more stakeholders. 8. The display device for vehicles of claim 7, wherein the one or more stakeholders comprises a stakeholder from the following group of stakeholders: (i) a licence authority; (ii) a parent; (iii) a caretaker; and (iv) a driving instructor. 9. The display device for vehicles of claim 6, wherein the logbook is stored in the memory of the Controller. 10. The display device for vehicles of claim 6, wherein the logbook is stored in the memory of the remote device. 1 1.The display device for vehicles of claim 6, wherein the logbook is stored in a remote cloud storage. 12. The display device for vehicles of claim 5, wherein the user profile module includes information about the respective display region corresponding to the user's license information. 13. The display device for vehicles of claims 5, wherein the user module is configured to connect with the controller and automatically trigger the controller to display the one of the plurality of display region corresponding to the userâs license information. 14. The display device for vehicles of claims 13, wherein the user module configured to connect with the controller when the distance between the user and the vehicles is within the range of 1 meter to 10 meters enabling a user to ensure correct display region is displayed before entering inside of the vehicle. 15. The display device for vehicles of claim 13, wherein the user profile module is configured to communicate with the controller by using near field communication techniques, including but not limited to Bluetooth and infrared (IR). 16. The display device for vehicles of claim 5, wherein the remote device is a handheld device. 17. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 further comprising a mounting rig, the mounting rig having at least two arms, each arm having first end regions attachable to a license plate or fitting of a vehicle and second end regions attachable to the housing. 18. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the housing further comprises a detachable cover to provide selective access to the interior of the housing, the detachable cover comprising a fastening means to securely attach the detachable cover to the housing. 19. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the housing further comprises a silicone casing, the silicone casing being configured to cover at least a portion of the housing. 20. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the transparent material is an acrylic sheet. 21 .The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the housing further comprises a motor housing to secure the motor onto the interior of the housing. 22. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the motor is a stepper motor. 23. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the first and second rotators are gears and the motor is mechanically connected to the first rotator and second rotator by a plurality of supporting gears. 24. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the motor is mechanically connected to the first rotator by a first chain and the second rotator by a second chain. 25. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein the first rotator and the second rotator have the same diameter. 26. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein each of the plurality of display regions have the same dimensions. 27. The display device for vehicles of claim 26, wherein the computer executable instructions are configured to cause the processor to activate the motor to angularly displace the first rotator by a predetermined number of degrees of rotation only such that another of the plurality of display regions is completely displayed through the transparent material. 28. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein at least one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a learner driver. 29. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein at least one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a provisional driver. 30. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein at least one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a returning driver. 31. The display device for vehicles of claim 1 , wherein one of the plurality of display regions displays a blank area. 32. A method of displaying a display region of a display sheet, comprising steps of: a. sending of a first computer-executable instruction to a controller from a remote device activated by a user; b. executing of the computer-executable instruction by a processor of the controller to activate a motor; c. rotating of a first shaft, the first shaft comprising a first rotator mechanically connected to the motor, wherein the rotation of the first shaft corresponds to a user input; 

 d. scrolling of a display sheet, the display sheet comprising a plurality of display regions, a first end region and a second end region, the first end region of the display sheet being detachably attached to the first shaft in such a way that when the first shaft rotates, the display sheet either rolls onto the first shaft or unrolls outward the first shaft, and at conclusion of the motor activation, a single display region is visible. 33. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, further comprising steps of providing a second shaft and a second rotator, wherein the second rotator is configured to rotate a first end region of the second shaft; connecting the second rotator to the first rotator such that rotation of the first rotator causes the second rotator to rotate in the same direction; and detachably attaching a second end region of the display sheet to the second shaft such that rotation of the second shaft results in the display sheet either rolling onto the second shaft or unrolling outward from the second shaft. 34. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, further comprising steps of storing data of the dimensions of the display regions in the memory; and determining the total degrees of rotation needed to change from one to another display region, until one of the plurality of display regions is completely displayed by processing the data by the processor. 35. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 34, further comprising steps of actuating the rotation of the motor by the processor when the user remotely activates the controller through the remote device; and stopping automatically the rotation of the motor based on the stored data of dimensions of the display regions to completely display one of the plurality of display regions. 36. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32 wherein one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a learning driver. 37. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32 wherein one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a provisional driver. 38. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, wherein one of the plurality of display regions displays a symbol associated with a returning driver. 39. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, wherein one of the plurality of display regions displays a blank slate. 40. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, further comprising a step of automatically scrolling the display sheet by a user module of the remote device operated by the user. 41. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 40, further comprising steps of tracking data related to date, time, and distance travelled by the user when each of the plurality of display regions is in use; and recording the data in a logbook. 42. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 41 , further comprising a step of transmitting the data from the logbook to one or more stakeholders. 43. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 42, wherein the one or more stakeholders comprises a stakeholder from the following group of stakeholders: (i) a licence authority; (ii) a parent; (iii) a caretaker; and (iv) a driving instructor. 44. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 41 , wherein the logbook is stored in the memory of the Controller. 45. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 41 , wherein the logbook is stored in the memory of the remote device. 46. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 41 , wherein the logbook is stored in a remote cloud storage. 47. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 40, wherein the user profile module includes information about the respective display region corresponding to the user's license information. 48. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 40, further comprising steps of connecting the user module with the controller; and triggering the controller automatically to display the one of the plurality of display region corresponding to the userâs license information. 49. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 48, wherein the user module configured to connect with the controller when the distance between the user and the vehicle is within the range of 1 meter to 10 meters enabling a user to ensure correct display region is displayed before entering inside of the vehicle. 50. The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 48, wherein the user profile module is configured to communicate with the controller by using near field communication techniques, including but not limited to Bluetooth and infrared (IR). 51 . The method of displaying a display region of a display sheet of claim 32, wherein the remote device is a handheld device.
